1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:07,500
Cryo-electron tomography turns raw movies of a cell
into molecular maps inside that cell.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:14,500
Normally it's a week of babysitting a dozen tools.
Here — you hand it off.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:22,000
First checkpoint. It doesn't ask you to trust it —
it shows you:

4
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:31,000
every tomogram reconstructed, one QC agent each,
a handedness check so downstream poses aren't mirrored.

5
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:37,000
Ten of ten. You sign off.

6
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:57,000
Next checkpoint: it finds the molecules.
Template matching, scored —

7
00:00:57,500 --> 00:01:07,000
and the QC tells good tomograms from bad: here the picks
follow the cell; there, the strongest hits sit on an ice
edge — so that tomogram is out.

8
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:17,000
Then the same tools, a new config, no new code —
and it finds a second, much rarer machine,
at ninety-seven-percent recall.

9
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:24,000
The payoff checkpoint.
Which of these twenty blobs are real ribosomes?

10
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:32,000
One score would mislead you — a low-res template loves
a smooth blob, and ranks the sharpest maps last.

11
00:01:32,500 --> 00:01:41,000
So it brings four measurements, mostly template-free,
and shows you where they agree and where they fight.

12
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:51,000
It names the confident core, flags the ambiguous cluster —
instead of hiding it. Then it steps back. You decide.

13
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:13,000
Resolution, measured honestly — the mask can fake signal,
so it randomizes the phases and subtracts that off.

14
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:23,000
Then both molecules go into one refinement population,
so the tilt-series model is solved with every particle
from both —

15
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:31,000
ribosomes anchor the geometry, and the rare species
rides along.

16
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:40,000
The result: a ribosome at seven-point-eight ångströms,
and fatty-acid synthase at fourteen — its D-three barrel, resolved.

17
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:48,000
Then both maps go back where they live — every molecule,
at its pose, inside the cell.

18
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:54,000
Molecular sociology, read straight off the data.

19
00:02:55,000 --> 00:03:00,000
State on disk, not chat. Gates for judgment.
An agent you supervise — not a script you babysit.
